American socialite Kim Kardashian has revealed what led to her divorce from Kanye West. The model, who graced the March 2022 cover of Vogue Magazine, in an interview with Jen Wang, said some changes were created at the cost of her marriage. The mother-of-four explained unequivocally she decided to choose herself and no longer other people at the expense of her marriage although she didn’t mind because she feels good and happier too. “For so long, I did what made other people happy. And I think in the last two years I decided, I’m going to make myself happy. And that feels really good.   Buhari orders sanction of adulterated fuel suppliers     American rapper Eve welcomes first child with hubby     UPDATED: Four dead as robbers attack bullion van in Ibadan   - Advertisement - “And even if that created changes and caused my divorce, I think it’s important to be honest with yourself about what really makes you happy. I’ve chosen myself. I think it’s okay to choose you,” she said. Continuing, the 41-year-old billionaire businesswoman said her forties will be about being “Team Me” adding, she’ll do anything she has to in a bid to stay happy. “My 40s are about being Team Me. I’m going to eat well. I’m going to work out. I’m going to have more fun, spend more time with my kids and the people who make me happy. I’m going to put my phone down. Unfollow if I don’t want to see something on Instagram,” she added.